					<div class="columnnist-img"><img src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/newdesign/assets/images/bg/default-pic-w600.jpg" class="lazy" data-src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1565759115.jpg" alt="User-unfriendly Mor Prom app a flop" title="User-unfriendly Mor Prom app a flop"  data-srcset="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1565759115_32.jpg 350w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1565759115_32.jpg 500w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1565759115_32.jpg 700w"  ></div>					<div class="columnnist-name">BY <a href="/opinion/columnist/811" class="link-unterline">Paritta Wangkiat</a></div>
				</div>
				<!--div class="h-line"><a href=""></a></div-->
				<h3><a href="/opinion/opinion/2120375/user-unfriendly-mor-prom-app-a-flop">User-unfriendly Mor Prom app a flop</a>
								</h3>
				<p>Two months ago, the Public Health Ministry announced an ambitious plan to use &quot;Mor Prom,&quot; a Line account and mobile application to manage Covid vaccine registrations. Mor Prom is not just another mobile app. The ministry is reported to have adopted artificial intelligence (AI) technology to assist in Covid vaccine registration, dubbed to be the largest mass vaccination in Thai history, to be smooth and seamless.</p>
				<div class="f-icon">
				<span class="fa-date-showmobi">24 May 2021 </span>	<!-- show mobile -->
				<span class="ic-comment"><a href="/opinion/opinion/2120375/user-unfriendly-mor-prom-app-a-flop?view_comment=1"><i class="icon-comment"></i> 47</a></span>							  </div>
			</div>
			<div class="listnews-img"><a href="/opinion/opinion/2120375/user-unfriendly-mor-prom-app-a-flop"><img src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/newdesign/assets/images/bg/default-pic-w600.jpg" class="img-fluid lazy" data-src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/dcx/2021/05/24/3982007.jpg" title="User-unfriendly Mor Prom app a flop" alt="User-unfriendly Mor Prom app a flop"  data-srcset="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/dcx/2021/05/24/3982007_126.jpg 350w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/dcx/2021/05/24/3982007_216.jpg 500w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/dcx/2021/05/24/3982007_216.jpg 700w"  ></a></div>		</div>
	</div>


<div class="listnews-row noimage">
	
		<div class="listnews-col-left">
			<div class="listnews-datetime">24 May 2021 </div>	<!-- show desktop -->
		</div>
		<div class="listnews-col-right">
			<div class="listnews-text">
				<div class="listnews-opinion">
					<div class="columnnist-img"><img src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/newdesign/assets/images/bg/default-pic-w600.jpg" class="lazy" data-src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1608889895.jpg" alt="Leading by serving, not ruling" title="Leading by serving, not ruling"  data-srcset="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1608889895_32.jpg 350w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1608889895_32.jpg 500w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1608889895_32.jpg 700w"  ></div>					<div class="columnnist-name">BY <a href="/opinion/columnist/968" class="link-unterline">Peerasit Kamnuansilpa</a></div>
				</div>
				<!--div class="h-line"><a href=""></a></div-->
				<h3><a href="/opinion/opinion/2120447/leading-by-serving-not-ruling">Leading by serving, not ruling</a>
								</h3>
				<p>About two weeks ago, through a Facebook group, more than half a million Thais expressed a desire to leave Thailand to settle down in countries such as the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom, Germany, Sweden, Norway, Australia and New Zealand, among others.</p>
				<div class="f-icon">
				<span class="fa-date-showmobi">24 May 2021 </span>	<!-- show mobile -->
				<span class="ic-comment"><a href="/opinion/opinion/2120447/leading-by-serving-not-ruling?view_comment=1"><i class="icon-comment"></i> 3</a></span>							  </div>
			</div>
					</div>
	</div>


<div class="listnews-row noimage">
	
		<div class="listnews-col-left">
			<div class="listnews-datetime">24 May 2021 </div>	<!-- show desktop -->
		</div>
		<div class="listnews-col-right">
			<div class="listnews-text">
				<div class="listnews-opinion">
					<div class="columnnist-img"><img src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/newdesign/assets/images/bg/default-pic-w600.jpg" class="lazy" data-src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/12841443416083.jpg" alt="When robots will be caring for humans" title="When robots will be caring for humans"  data-srcset="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/12841443416083_32.jpg 350w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/12841443416083_32.jpg 500w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/12841443416083_32.jpg 700w"  ></div>					<div class="columnnist-name">BY <a href="/opinion/columnist/1284" class="link-unterline">Gwynne Dyer</a></div>
				</div>
				<!--div class="h-line"><a href=""></a></div-->
				<h3><a href="/opinion/opinion/2120455/when-robots-will-be-caring-for-humans">When robots will be caring for humans</a>
								</h3>
				<p>The birth rates are falling fast in all the world&#039;s more prosperous countries, but the generation now in their middle years have not yet grasped what that means for their later years. If they end up needing some sort of assisted living, either at home or in a care home, they will probably be looked after by a robot.</p>
				<div class="f-icon">
				<span class="fa-date-showmobi">24 May 2021 </span>	<!-- show mobile -->
											  </div>
			</div>
					</div>
	</div>


<div class="listnews-row ">
	
		<div class="listnews-col-left">
			<div class="listnews-datetime">24 May 2021 </div>	<!-- show desktop -->
		</div>
		<div class="listnews-col-right">
			<div class="listnews-text">
				<div class="listnews-opinion">
										<div class="columnnist-name">BY <a href="https://search.bangkokpost.com/search/result_advanced?category=news&columnistName=Piyanut+Kotsan" class="link-unterline">Piyanut Kotsan</a></div>
				</div>
				<!--div class="h-line"><a href=""></a></div-->
				<h3><a href="/opinion/opinion/2120459/pandemic-shows-need-for-new-approach-to-protest">Pandemic shows need for new approach to protest</a>
								</h3>
				<p>Thailand&#039;s youth protesters are facing many criminal charges brought on by the authorities, including for allegedly violating the state of emergency in place to curb the spread of Covid-19. Some who were jailed, in fact, caught Covid-19 while in prison.</p>
				<div class="f-icon">
				<span class="fa-date-showmobi">24 May 2021 </span>	<!-- show mobile -->
				<span class="ic-comment"><a href="/opinion/opinion/2120459/pandemic-shows-need-for-new-approach-to-protest?view_comment=1"><i class="icon-comment"></i> 46</a></span>							  </div>
